name: Foil-Pouch Grilled Green Beans
author: Nathan Shobe
summary: Trying out different grilling techniques for vegetables.
ingredients: ½ pound fresh green beans, trimmed
directions: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate
Layer 2 sheets of aluminum foil on a work surface
Toss together green beans and olive oil in a bowl until coated; season with salt and pepper
Place mixture on top of the prepared sheets of foil
Add water, and bring the edges of the foil over the vegetables, sealing to create a pouch
Place the foil pouch on the preheated grill and cook until beans are tender, about 15 minutes
